Installation Instructions
=========================

Prerequisites:
 - Python 2.6 or later (Python 2.x series)
 - mpmath (optional, but 10x faster than python's built in decimal module)
          http://code.google.com/p/mpmath/, 
	  packaged as python-mpmath in debian based distros
	  (bundled with sympy in fedora?)


Installation Methods
--------------------

Method 1: Install using pip (recommended)
------------------------------------------
From the repository root directory:

    pip install .

Or, to include the optional fast mpmath dependency:

    pip install .[fast]

For development installation (editable mode):

    pip install -e .


Method 2: Install using setup.py
---------------------------------
From the repository root directory:

    python setup.py install


Method 3: Run from source tree (legacy method)
-----------------------------------------------
You can still run BBChop from the source tree without installation.
You need to set PYTHONPATH to point at the source dir, eg:

    PYTHONPATH=/path/to/BBChop/source bbchop


Verifying Installation
----------------------
After installation, you should be able to run:

    bbchop

This will display the usage information.


